summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming resolutions on Côte d’Ivoire, particularly 1514 (2003), 1498 (2003), and 1464 (2003),
Reaffirming commitment to Côte d’Ivoire's sovereignty, independence, territorial integrity, and unity,
Reaffirming endorsement of the Linas-Marcoussis Agreement, 
Stressing complete and unconditional implementation of the Agreement,
Recalling support for ECOWAS and France's efforts,
Noting progress made, 
Taking note of the President of Côte d’Ivoire’s request to transform MINUCI into a peacekeeping operation,
Noting the need for MINUCI to continue its mandate,
Affirming readiness to consider Secretary-General’s report,
Noting challenges to Côte d’Ivoire's stability and threat to international peace and security,
Acting under Chapter VII,
1. Extends MINUCI's mandate until 27 February 2004;
2. Renews authorization for Member States participating in ECOWAS forces and French Forces until 27 February 2004;
3. Takes note of the Secretary-General's report;
4. Calls on Linas-Marcoussis Agreement signatories to fulfill responsibilities;
5. Calls on signatories to take steps recommended by the Secretary-General;
6. Requests Secretary-General to prepare possible peacekeeping operation deployment within five weeks;
7. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
